#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Ambapālivagga "
msgstr "1. In Ambapālī’s Wood "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Satisutta → satosuttaṃ (bj) | sato (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Satisutta "
msgstr "2. Mindful "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.142, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati ambapālivane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, in Ambapālī’s Wood. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn47.2:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.2:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.2:2.1"
msgid "“Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vihareyya sampajāno. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant should live mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī. "
msgstr "This is my instruction to you. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.2:2.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant mindful? "

msgctxt "sn47.2:2.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:2.5"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.2:2.6"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.2:2.7"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is mindful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.2:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant aware? "

msgctxt "sn47.2:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent. "

# NOTE: Note that here, as elsewhere, the closing phrase is worded differently than the opening.
msgctxt "sn47.2:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajānakārī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant acts with situational awareness. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:3.4"
msgid "Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vihareyya sampajāno. "
msgstr "A mendicant should live mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "sn47.2:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti. "
msgstr "This is my instruction to you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.2:3.6"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

